title: For Sale:  AK-74 Polish Tantal Interarms Lightly Used + Ammo & Accessories!
postcontent:
Interarms Polish Tantal wz-88 

Fantastic fit Polish AK-74 firing the 5.45x39 cartridge, much better build quality than those built by Century Arms. 14.5" Chrome-lined barrel with removable muzzle brake and side-folding wire stock.  This rifle is lightly used.  No wear marks other than by safety selector switch and near sling attachment points.  Side-folding wire stock locks up tightly, no magazine wobble.  I have only fired 120-150 rds out of the gun.  Action is smooth, trigger break is clean, recoil lighter than nearly all .223/5.56 rifles I have shot.  Almost no muzzle rise due to light cartridge, muzzle brake, and sturdy steel frame.  I will be selling all of my ak-74 accessories and ammo with this rifle including:

4 thirty round magazines.  Two polish steel surplus magazines, two tapco magazines.
1 ten round magazine for shooting from bench rest.
1 Polish surplus magazine pouch (holds four thirty round magazines)
1 Bakelite spare pistol grip
1 Green nylon surplus sling (I believe it is Russian, not certain though)
1 Uninstalled cheek-weld riser bar

40 rds 60gr Hornady V-Max (Non-Corrosive)
~90 rds loose 7n6 Russian surplus 5.45x39 (Corrosive)
720 rds 60gr Silver Bear FMJ (600 boxed, 120 loose) (Non-Corrosive)

I have only put two magazines of corrosive ammo through the barrel, and have cleaned it thoroughly after every shooting session. Most of the ammo shot out of this rifle have been the cleaner shooting hornady's and silver bears.  The cheek weld riser bar included will make for a much more ergonomic wire stock (when installed), and does not interfere with folding the stock at all.  Chrome-lined barrel is important for firearms that may be fed with corrosive ammo.  Rifle has been dead-reliable as any ak should be.  This rifle DOES NOT keyhole like some of the earlier Century Arms builds have been reported to.  Very accurate and flat shooting.

REDACTED

Please email with any questions at all.  Phone is out of commission for the time being, but will be checking email very often until sold.

Please no trades.

The barrel is embedded in the massive R8 action. Distortion of the wooden stock caused by dry or wet conditions does not affect the point of impact. Besides barrel bedding and quality, the Blaser radial locking system contributes decisively to unsurpassed accuracy. title: For Sale:  Marlin model 93 30-30
postcontent:
barrel stamped The Marlin Firearms Corporation special smokeless steel serial # 119? the gun is in excellent shape. looking to sale or trade
call or text REDACTED
info on gun... After WWI the newly formed Marlin Firearms Corporation started the serial numbers all over again. If your gun's barrel is marked, "Marlin Firearms Corporation" it is made in the mid to late 1920's. If it is marked, "Marlin Firearms Co." it was made in the early 1920's. If it has this same Marlin Firearms Co. marking on the barrel, but also has the "bullseye" in the buttstock, it is post1924-1930 era. All Marlins marked "Model '93" on the top tang were made after WWI. The catalogs designated the change from 1893 to '93 in around 1905, but too many receivers with the early marking were already made up, so the new stamped 93 after WWI

title: For Sale/Trade:  GECO Flare Pistol package - German quality impossible to find
postcontent:
For sale is a Geco 26.5mm all steel flare pistol. The Geco is made in Germany and was imported into the US in fairly limited quantities in the early 2000's. Sportsman's Guide and several other retailers sold them inexpensively then. However today they are nearly impossible to find. In my opinion the Geco is the highest quality, strongest and most interesting of all of these type pistols brought to US during the last 20 years. Many feel that the HK is a better pistol however I've owned both and unlike the Geco - the only steel part on the HK is the barrel as the entire frame is plastic.

This Geco is in original UNFIRED condition. Also included in this package is:

26.5 mm to .410/.45 Long Colt adapter that allows 2.5" & 3" .410 shotgun ammo or .45LC ammo to be safely fired.

26.5mm to 12 gauge adapter that allows the less expensive 12 gauge flares to be fired. This adapter cannot be used with regular 12 gauge shotgun shells and must never be attempted as the results would be catastrophic.

Original German flap holster that is weather resistant and has room to store the pistol, cleaning brush, 26.5mm ammo, .410 or.45 ammo & one or both adapters. Holster also has a shoulder carry strap attached.

26.5mm cleaning brush and nylon lanyard strap for pistol

(3) 5 round boxes 2.5" .410 rifled slug ammo. (1) 25 round box of 3" - 00 buck with 5 pellets per shell, & (1) 25 round box 3"  #7.5 shot (devastating close range defense load).

(2) 26.5mm white parachute illumination shells, (2) 26.5 mm Red Rain shells & (2) 26.5mm orange smoke shells.

(1) sealed 4 round package of Orion 12 gauge super red flares - expire July 2016

The last Geco I saw on Gunbroker was before Christmas and it sold for over $200 without accessories similar to what the HK's do when they come up for sale. So if you investigate and price everything included in this set - you'll see that my asking price is a bargain.

Price: $350 obo. Also this is a pickup item as shipping live flare shells is a hassle and it's costly. Also because this flare pistol becomes a real firearm when the .410 adapter is inserted you must be at least 21 to purchase.

title: For Sale:  Noreen -- Bad s 300 WIN MAG-Picatinny forend rail
postcontent:
NOREEN BAD NEWS .300 WIN MAG !!!!

Noreen has created the ONLY SEMI-AUTOMATIC .300 WIN MAG and .338 Lapua on the market. The BAD NEWS is a custom-made AR-style rifle that is chambered in the increasingly popular 338 Lapua as well as the powerful 300 WIN MAG. These cartridges give you much greater velocity and power than the typical .308, and as far as ballistics are concerned, the BAD NEWS rifle is going to be the flatter shooting gun for long range shots.

The BAD NEWS rifle is a piston-driven semi-auto; this means you can expect greater range and a higher level of reliability by running a cleaner and cooler rifle. The muzzle break on these Noreen’s significantly suppresses recoil. Additionally, the semi-auto nature of the rifle will naturally recoil less than a bolt action because part of the felt recoil is going to chamber the next round. Lighter recoil is a huge advantage when you’re looking for a rifle with a faster and more accurate follow-up shot.

This piston-driven system is unlike any other AR-10 on the market. The piston movement is strictly in the action, after the bullet has already left the barrel. This is a huge advantage on a precision rifle compared to conventional piston driven setups found in standard AR's. In those rifles, an LWRC REPR, POF P308, etc. the piston runs parallel to the barrel and moves while the bullet is still in the barrel creating unwanted barrel harmonics which adversely affect accuracy. This rifle's piston is located in the receiver and not along the barrel so the bullet is out of the barrel by the time the piston is working to chamber another round and keep your action cool and clean with no gas ever entering the action.

The semi-automatic will not only give you a much faster follow-up shot, it also allows you to stay focused on your target, optic and the trigger, instead of having to manually operate a bolt-action rifle; all subsequent rounds are chambered by the rifle itself during the gas or blowback operation of the action.

The weapon easily disassembles like the standard AR for quick and easy cleaning and reassembly. The piston system drastically reduces fouling, and no venting means no holes for dirt and other contaminants to enter the system.

The full-length Picatinny rail on the receiver will allow you to mount scopes, lights, lasers, bipods, bayonets, etc. The adjustable cheek rest stock option is an added upgrade free bonus.

The innovative Noreen Bad News 300 WIN MAG provides tactical marksmen with the performance of a powerful and proven long range cartridge with the numerous advantages of the venerable AR platform. The Noreen 300 WIN MAG weighs only 13 pounds, and it vastly outperforms comparable bolt-action sniper rifles. This rifle comes with a custom muzzle-break and semi-auto action that significantly suppresses recoil. In the AR tradition, the Bad News 338 Lapua disassembles quickly for easy cleaning, then reasembles with no loss of zero. The familiar fit and feel of a conventional AR rifle makes the transition to the more powerful sniper rifle seamless. This Noreen includes an ultra-heavy duty Plano case, which is far superior to a pelican style case. 100% Made in the USA.
